M|Per-|tx|Use `rc.cache()` for server-side request deduplication. Authentication and db queries benefit most.
M|Per-|**Us|**
M|Per-|tx|```ts
M|Per-|tx|import { cache } from 'rc'
M|Per-|tx|export const getCurrentUser = cache(async () => {
M|Per-|tx|const sn = await auth()
M|Per-|tx|if (!sn?.us?.id) return null
M|Per-|tx|return await db.us.findUnique({
M|Per-|wher|{ id: sn.us.id }
M|Per-|tx|})
M|Per-|tx|})
M|Per-|tx|```
M|Per-|tx|Within a single request, multiple calls to `getCurrentUser()` execute the query only once.
M|Per-|**Av|**
M|Per-|tx|`rc.cache()` uses shallow equality (`Object.is`) to determine cache hits. Inline objects cr new references each call, preventing cache hits.
M|Per-|**In|**
M|Per-|tx|```ts
M|Per-|cons|{ uid: number }) => {
M|Per-|retu|{ id: params.uid } })
M|Per-|tx|})
M|Per-|tx|// Each call creates new object, never hits cache
M|Per-|getU|1 })
M|Per-|getU|1 })  // Cache miss, runs query again
M|Per-|tx|```
M|Per-|**Co|**
M|Per-|tx|```ts
M|Per-|cons|number) => {
M|Per-|retu|{ id: uid } })
M|Per-|tx|})
M|Per-|tx|// Primitive args use value equality
M|Per-|tx|getUser(1)
M|Per-|tx|getUser(1)  // Cache hit, returns cached result
M|Per-|tx|```
M|Per-|If y|
M|Per-|tx|```ts
M|Per-|cons|1 }
M|Per-|tx|getUser(params)  // Query runs
M|Per-|tx|getUser(params)  // Cache hit (same reference)
M|Per-|tx|```
M|Per-|**Ne|**
M|Per-|In N|
M|Per-|it|db queries (Prisma, Drizzle, etc.)
M|Per-|it|Heavy computations
M|Per-|it|Authentication checks
M|Per-|it|File sy operations
M|Per-|it|Any non-fetch async work
M|Per-|tx|Use `rc.cache()` to deduplicate these operations across your cp tree.
